    {
      "id": "9e4f8a6797735e2ec451bc01ab7ed056ae2c8b56",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2025-03-30 04:30:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis patch is only half of what is needed, since I don't know the complexities of Perl.\n\nI need it to iterate the $spelling_suspects list and match all of the keys against $typo, and if it matches then look up $suspect to get the right $typo_fix string.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "08eeb0a1ccae7f07f8d61ffeb7b3c831b369c9d5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2025-03-30 16:52:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI've been seeing these 'CHECKPATCH ERROR's a lot more often recently. https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/58439 seems to hit quite a few of them. Any idea what changed? Weird entries in spelling.txt?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "22579b2d613e1bd1cf5af1569faadc67dc46cc13",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2025-03-30 17:29:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes, it is the \"%.*s\" entry, which is matching anything with \"%s\" in it. It should be \"%\\.\\*s\" to match the literal '.' and '*' for strings that may not be NUL-terminated. \n\nI've fixed that in the spelling.txt in this patch, but the problem with the regexp matching still remains. The issue is that \"$typo\" is the matched string, but not the regexp that is needed to find the $typo_fix in the spelling_fix array. \n\nWhat is still needed is some Perl-fu to iterate the spelling_suspects array, find the regexp that matched the $typo and then use that to look up the typo_fix.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "dc44839597934f300be21f6b48663773834d1f99",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2025-03-30 17:31:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI suppose the DNAME regexp and other spelling.txt fixes could be landed separately for the checkpatch.pl fix. That would at least reduce the frequency of this error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
